File: South Africa has just under a 156,000 active cases at the moment. JOHANNESBURG - Nearly 7 out of every 10 South Africans who tested positive for COVID-19 have already recovered. This means the country has just under a 156,000 active cases at the moment. The health department reported 213 new COVID-19 related deaths in the last 24 hours. Fifty-one patients died in the Free State, 43 in the Western Cape, 40 in Gauteng, 31 in KZN, 25 in the Eastern Cape and 23 in Limpopo. READ: COVID-19: Ramaphosa vows to tackle corruption Just under 8,200 new cases have been reported in the last 24 hours. More than 3-million tests have been conducted since the outbreak started in March. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.